The '''Meerasaheb dargah''' is a common [[worship]] centre for both [[Muslim]] and [[Hindu]] [[communities]] located near the railway station of [[Miraj]]. 

Thousands of [[people]] flock to [[Dargah]] on every Thursday morning to get the [[blessing]]s of Hazarat Meerasaheb and his son Hazarat Shamsuddin Hussein.
Hazrat Meerasaheb was a great [[Sufism|Sufi]] [[saint]] of his time.It is said that on the command of  Allah he migrated to [[India]] from [[Mecca]] (Saudi Arabia). He propagated [[Islam]] through his life. Every year URS (martyrdom day) is celebrated with millions of people visits this [[shrine]] for offering their [[salutes]].{{fact|date=June 2017}}

