{{Infobox temple | name = Hindu Temple of Minnesota | image = | alt = | caption = | map_type = USA Minnesota | map_caption = Location in Minnesota | coordinates = {{coord|45.146346|-93.511142|type:landmark_region:US-MN|display=inline,title}} | other_names = | proper_name = | country = United States | state = [[Minnesota]] | location = [[Maple Grove, Minnesota|Maple Grove]] | elevation_m = | deity = | primary_deity_Godess = | utsava_deity_God = | utsava_deity_Godess= | Direction_posture = | Pushakarani = | Vimanam = | Poets = | Prathyaksham = | festivals= | address = | architecture = | temple_quantity = | monument_quantity= | inscriptions = | year_completed = 2006 | creator = | website = {{URL|https://www.hindumandirmn.org/}} }}
'''Hindu Temple of Minnesota''' is a [[Hindu Temple]] located in [[Maple Grove, Minnesota|Maple Grove]] serving the over 40,000 hindus in the [[Minneapolis Metropolitan Area]]. It has a floor space of over 43,000 square feet, making it one of the largest Hindu temples in the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.minneapolisnorthwest.com/directory/hindu-mandir-the-hindu-temple-of-minnesota/|website = Minneapolis Northwest|title = Hindu Mandir The Hindu Temple of Minnesota|access-date = 18 November 2018}}</ref> It has the capacity to accommodate up to 5,000 people at one time.
==History== The Hindu Temple was vandalized in 2005 during a $9 million expansion plan to build multiple temples.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.mprnews.org/story/2006/07/14/hindutemple|website = mprnews|title = Hindu Temple rises from a Minnesota Cornfield|date = 14 July 2006|author = Crann, Tom|access-date = 18 November 2018}}</ref> Currently, the temple is planning to develop a nearby 60 acre plot of land for use for various buildings such as senior condos and a yoga retreat center.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.startribune.com/hindu-temple-has-big-plans-for-60-acres-in-maple-grove/408912065/|website = Star Tribune|title = Hindu Temple has Big Plans for 60 acres in Maple Grove|date = 16 December 2016|access-date = 18 November 2018}}</ref>
