{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = | name = Josef Stangl | honorific-suffix = | title = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Würzburg|Bishop of Würzburg]] | image = Josef Stangl 1962.jpg | alt = | caption = | church = | archdiocese = | province = | metropolis = | diocese = | see = | appointed =27 June 1957 | elected = | term_start = 12 September 1957 | quashed = | term_end = 8 January 1979 | predecessor = [[Julius August Döpfner]] | successor = [[Paul-Werner Scheele]] | opposed = | other_post = <!---------- Orders ----------> | ordination = 16 March 1930 | consecration =12 September 1957 | consecrated_by = [[Josef Schneider (bishop)|Josef Schneider]] | cardinal = | rank = <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = Josef Stangl | birth_date = {{birth date|1907|03|12|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Kronach]], [[German Empire]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1979|04|08|1907|03|12|df=y}} | death_place = [[Schweinfurt]], [[West Germany]] | buried = | nationality = German | religion = [[Roman Catholic]] | residence = | parents = | spouse = | children = | occupation = | profession = | alma_mater = | signature = <!---------- Sainthood ----------> | coat_of_arms = WappenStangl.jpg | motto = domino plebem perfectam | feast_day = | venerated = | saint_title = | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | attributes = | patronage = | shrine = | suppressed_date = <!---------- Other ----------> | other = | imagesize = | ordinated_by = }}
'''Josef Stangl''' ({{IPA-de|ˈʃtaŋl̩|lang}}; 12 March 1907 &ndash; 8 April 1979) was [[Roman Catholic]] [[bishop]] of [[Würzburg]], [[Germany]].
Born in [[Kronach]], [[Bavaria]], Stangl became a [[priest]] on 16 March 1930, and he was appointed by [[Pope Pius XII]] as [[Bishop of Würzburg]] on 27 June 1957.
He approved the [[exorcism]] on [[Anneliese Michel]] in 1975 and 1976, ordering total secrecy,<ref name="TWS">{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=s1s_AAAAIBAJ&sjid=yVIMAAAAIBAJ&pg=1378,1341502&hl=en|title=Priests convinced woman was possessed|publisher=[[The Windsor Star]]|accessdate=14 May 2011|date=4 April 1978}}</ref> "after careful consideration and good information" by Father Arnold Renz. She died of malnutrition from almost a year of semi-starvation while the rites of exorcism were performed.
Stangl [[Consecration#Ordination of bishops|consecrated]] Father Joseph Ratzinger, later [[Pope Benedict XVI]], as a bishop on 28 May 1977.
On 8 January 1979, Stangl withdrew as a bishop of Würzburg, and died in [[Schweinfurt]] in April 1979.
