In [[Aztec mythology]], '''Mictlanpachecatl''' (pronounced mikt-*lawn-pah-chey-kottle) is the god of the [[North wind]]. His brothers are [[Cihuatecayotl]], [[Tlalocayotl]], and [[Huitztlampaehecatl]], who personify the winds from the [[West wind|west]], [[East wind|east]], and [[South wind|south]] respectively.<ref>{{cite book|title=Diccionario de Mitología Nahua|editor=Biblioteca Porrúa. Imprenta del Museo Nacional de Arqueología, Historia y Etnología|authorlink=Cecilio Agustín Robelo|language=Spanish|year=1905|location=México|pages=168, 169|isbn=978-9684327955}}</ref>
