{{Speciesbox |image = Psilocybe caeruleoannulata Singer ex Guzmán 370804.jpg |genus = Psilocybe |species = caeruleoannulata |authority = [[Rolf Singer|Singer]] ex [[Gastón Guzmán|Guzmán]] (1978) |synonyms_ref = <ref name="Guzmán 1978"/> |synonyms = *''Stropharia siccipes'' var. ''lugubris'' <small>[[Johannes Rick|Rick]] (1939)</small> }}
'''''Psilocybe caeruleoannulata''''' is a species of [[psilocybin mushroom]] found in [[Uruguay]] and [[Brazil]], where it grows on [[marsh]]y grounds, [[grassland]]s, or [[pasture]]s.<ref name="Guzmán 1978"/> It is the most common ''[[Psilocybe]]'' species in the Floresta Nacional de São Francisco de Paula, in [[Rio Grande do Sul]], Brazil.<ref name="da Silva 2012"/>
